<Base title="Kraft Heinz / MiO — Case Study">

  <div class="section">
    <a class="breadcrumb" href="/Personal/case-studies/">← <span>Case Studies</span> / Kraft Heinz / MiO</a>
    <div class="cs-hero">[MiO digital shelf]</div>
    <div class="cs-tags"><span class="cs-tag">CPG</span><span class="cs-tag">eCommerce</span><span class="cs-tag">Creative Direction</span><span class="cs-tag">Enterprise</span></div>
    <div class="cs-title">Rebuilding MiO's digital shelf for Amazon, Kroger, and beyond</div>
    <div class="cs-subtitle">Led the eCommerce UX overhaul, creative system, and multi-channel asset production that drove a measurable sales lift on Amazon — while scaling the approach across 30+ KH brands.</div>
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Client</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Kraft Heinz (via Imaginary Content)</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Feb 2020 – Oct 2021</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Art Director</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">CPG / Enterprise eCommerce</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Lead Brand</div><div class="cs-meta-value">MiO</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">~8%</div><div class="stat-label">Amazon sales lift (MiO, YoY)</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">800+</div><div class="stat-label">Digital assets produced</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">15+</div><div class="stat-label">A+ and retailer pages built</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-kh-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-kh-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I did</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-kh-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-kh-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Strong product, weak shelf.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">MiO had strong brand recognition and a loyal customer base, but its digital shelf presence wasn't doing the product justice. The Amazon Brand Store was outdated. A+ content lacked structure. Kroger and retail media placements were inconsistent. And the creative system — across programmatic ads, Amazon carousel images, and retailer banners — had no unified logic connecting brand, UX, and conversion.<br /><br />This wasn't a design problem. It was a systems problem. Brand teams, retail teams, and media teams were all producing assets independently. The result was a fragmented shopping experience that looked different depending on where you found MiO — and none of it was optimized to actually sell.<br /><br />The broader context: MiO was one of ~30 Kraft Heinz brands I touched during this tenure. But MiO was the flagship project — the one where I owned the full digital shelf redesign end-to-end and where the results were tracked.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-kh-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Rebuilt the shelf as a system, not a set of pages.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body"><strong>A. Amazon A+ Content Redesign</strong> — Redesigned MiO's A+ content from scratch. Introduced structured content hierarchy: clear value proposition above the fold, competitive comparison module (0g sugar / 0 calories vs. juice, soda, and energy drinks), product line breakdown (Original, Energy, Vitamins, Sport), and FAQ section. Every module was designed for scan behavior and conversion — not brand storytelling for its own sake. The A+ template I built for MiO became the model for other KH brands.<br /><br /><strong>B. Amazon Brand Store (Desktop + Mobile)</strong> — Built the full MiO Brand Store experience on Amazon — hero banner system, product grid with lifestyle photography alternating with product shots, sub-brand navigation (Original / Energy / Vitamins / Sport), and category CTAs driving to product pages. Designed mobile-optimized versions of every component.<br /><br /><strong>C. Multi-Channel Creative System</strong> — Designed the MiO creative system across channels: Kroger web banners (desktop, mobile, sidebar — 6+ size variants per campaign), Amazon merch banners (3000x1200 hero format), programmatic display ads, and Amazon carousel/hero images for every SKU. Consistent visual language — the ink-in-water photography, product lineup compositions, and "We Fix Water" / "Bold Flavor" messaging — adapted to each channel's specs and constraints.<br /><br /><strong>D. Video + Motion</strong> — Storyboarded and created all graphics for the MiO animated product video for A+ content — showing the product in use and communicating the value prop visually in a scroll-heavy environment.<br /><br /><strong>E. Team and Execution</strong> — Directed a production designer and junior designer on the KH account (matrix, not formal reports). 99% digital channel mix — eCommerce, programmatic, retail media, social.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-kh-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Measurable lift, honest attribution.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">~8% Amazon sales lift on MiO — Kraft Heinz internal analytics, year-over-year same period. I led the digital shelf redesign during that window. I can speak to my contribution but can't isolate it from pricing, media spend, or competitive dynamics.<br /><br />15+ Amazon A+ and retailer pages designed from scratch. 800+ digital assets produced across eCommerce, programmatic, and retail channels. 100+ campaign visuals influenced. Full Amazon Brand Store designed and deployed (desktop + mobile). Kroger banner system designed across 6+ size variants. Animated product video storyboarded and produced for A+ content.<br /><br />The MiO redesign template scaled across the broader KH portfolio. What started as one brand's shelf overhaul became the system other brands adopted.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Key insight</div>
    <div class="foundation-card">
      <div class="foundation-section-title">The digital shelf isn't a design project. It's a revenue system.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc">Most eCommerce creative gets treated as production work — resize the banner, adapt the A+ template, ship the carousel images. What MiO needed was alignment: brand storytelling, conversion UX, and retail platform constraints all pulling in the same direction.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc" style="margin-bottom:0">The ~8% lift didn't come from making things look better. It came from making the entire shelf work as a system — from the Brand Store down to the last Kroger sidebar banner.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Selected assets</div>
